UN Secretary General Kofi Annan expressed deep concern over Nepal's democracy after King Gyanendra dismissed the government and imposed a state of emergency.
The EU and Japan also called for a return to democracy and release of detained leaders.
The US and UK condemned the king's actions, while China remained neutral.
Nepal's new home minister plans to resume peace talks with Maoists.
Despite international criticism, China respects Nepal's internal affairs.
Pakistan supports Nepal's sovereignty and hopes to reschedule the SAARC Summit.
The situation in Nepal remains tense, with a focus on restoring democracy and ending the Maoist rebellion.
